reason of the excessive nicety of their technicalities, the formulary system took their place, though in certain other cases they were retained. The essential feature of this system consisted in a formula, which the praetor (in iure) prepared aster hearing the parties to a suit, and which was remitted to the iudex to regulate his decision (in iudicio).
